First steps, first words, first birthdays.

One camcorder captured every little moment of Mark Christini's young Pennsylvania family from 1995 to 1998.

When he left it - and a bag of tapes - on a New Jersey beach during a holiday, they consigned themselves to the fact that all was lost.

But now, 16 years later, every single tape has been discovered in the disused attic of office owned by Jenkinson's Boardwalk, the beach.

